## 8. Setup & Local Run

```bash
# 1. Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/agro-advisory-agent.git
cd agro-advisory-agent

# 2. Set your Gemini API key (get one free at aistudio.google.com)
export GEMINI_API_KEY="your_key_here"

# 3. Install the Agents CLI
uvx google-agents-cli setup

# 4. (Optional) check available skills
agents-cli info

# 5. Install pre-commit hooks (Semgrep + formatting checks)
pre-commit install

# 6. Launch the local playground
agents-cli playground
```

Then open the printed `http://localhost:XXXX` URL in your browser to chat with
AgriGuard directly.

**No API keys or secrets are committed to this repo** — set `GEMINI_API_KEY` as an
environment variable as shown above.

## 9. Limitations & Future Work

- Currently runs locally via `agents-cli playground`; not deployed to a public
  endpoint for judging purposes (per competition rules, this isn't required). The
  graph nodes are largely stateless aside from session memory, so containerizing
  and deploying to Cloud Run would require minimal changes.
- Crop timing and market price data currently covers a limited set of
  districts/crops — expanding the JSON datasets is the most direct path to wider
  usefulness.
- No native Nepali-language support yet; this is a natural next addition given the
  target users.

